# Themis context workflow

At the start of every task, use these sources (do not rely on memory alone):

1. **`PROJECT_CONTEXT.md`** — domain model, three-layer data model, Clean Architecture, phase scope, quality gates, VEX invariants, API conventions.
2. **`README.md`** — build/test commands (`make check`), config env vars, coverage thresholds, repo structure.
3. **`openspec/`** — guardrails and implementation truth:
   - `openspec/changes/themis-phase-1/proposal.md` — scope and capabilities
   - `openspec/changes/themis-phase-1/design.md` — design decisions
   - `openspec/changes/themis-phase-1/tasks.md` — task groups and gates (mark complete only when gates pass)
   - `openspec/changes/themis-phase-1/specs/*/spec.md` — per-capability requirements

Also read **`AGENTS.md`** for the full context index.
Before final answers, complete **`verification.md`** (correctness, severity, observability).

## Rules

- Stay within **Phase 1** scope unless the user explicitly requests Phase 2/3 work.
- Follow Clean Architecture import direction; run `make check` before marking tasks done.
- Never delete or mutate raw `component_vulnerabilities` rows — VEX overlay only.
- Check the relevant OpenSpec spec before implementing a capability.
